rk is used to construct quasi-geologic models from which volumes\ncan be estimated directly. We apply the PGI framework to the magnetics and\ngravity data independently. The framework is also used to jointly invert these\ndata and produce a model that is consistent with both data sets. Cumulative\nvolume estimates with depth are informative and can help decide whether in situ\nor ex situ sequestration might be appropriate. Using each of the inverted\nmodels, we estimate cumulative volume of reactive rock as a function of depth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Mar 2022 20:10:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-29"}
